senses.sense_definition: Abbreviation for "as fuck"; used as an intensifier to mean extremely or very much.

examples.text: I am tired <w>af</w> after working a double shift today.
That new movie was funny <w>af</w>, we couldn't stop laughing.

senses.sense_definition: Abbreviation for Air Force, the branch of the military that fights using aircraft.

examples.text: He joined the <w>AF</w> immediately after graduating from high school.
The <w>AF</w> base is located just outside the city limits.

senses.sense_definition: Abbreviation for autofocus, a camera feature that automatically focuses the lens on a subject.

examples.text: My camera's <w>AF</w> struggles to lock onto subjects in low light.
Make sure the <w>AF</w> is turned on before you try to take a quick shot.

senses.sense_definition: Abbreviation for atrial fibrillation, a heart condition characterized by an irregular and often fast heartbeat.

examples.text: The patient was diagnosed with <w>AF</w> after complaining of heart palpitations.
Doctors prescribe blood thinners to reduce the stroke risk associated with <w>AF</w>.

senses.sense_definition: A derogatory term for a black African person.

examples.text: The historical novel depicted the racial tensions and how settlers referred to locals as <w>Afs</w>.
Using the term <w>Af</w> is considered highly offensive and unacceptable today.

senses.sense_definition: Abbreviation for antiferromagnetic, relating to a type of magnetism where adjacent ions align in opposite directions.

examples.text: The researcher studied the <w>AF</w> properties of the new oxide material.
In an <w>AF</w> state, the magnetic moments cancel each other out.
